<activity><title>Compound Interest</title>

<introduction><p>If <m>P</m> dollars is invested at an annual interest rate <m>r</m> (expressed as a decimal) compounded <m>n</m> times yearly, the balance of the account <m>A</m> after <m>t</m> years is given by  
      <me>A = P \left( 1 + \dfrac{r}{n} \right)^{nt}</me></p></introduction>

<task><p>If you invest $1000 at 10% compounded quarterly, how long will it take the balance to double?</p></task>

                <commentary audience="instructor"><title>Note</title>
                <p>You may need to explain that "quarterly" means four time per year.</p></commentary>
</activity>

